{
  "local_port": 33276,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the top rated Hollywood movies in 2017?",
  "response": "In 2017, Hollywood saw the release of a diverse range of films spanning various genres, many of which received critical acclaim and enjoyed significant audience popularity. Below are some of the top-rated Hollywood movies from that year, based on critical reviews, audience ratings, and cultural impact:\n\n1. **Get Out**\n   - **Genre:** Horror/Thriller\n   - **Director:** Jordan Peele\n   - **Synopsis:** A socially conscious horror film that blends suspense with sharp commentary on race relations. It follows a young African-American man who uncovers disturbing secrets when he meets his white girlfriend's family.\n   - **Highlights:** Acclaimed for its originality, direction, and screenplay. It won the Academy Award for Best Original Screenplay.\n\n2. **The Shape of Water**\n   - **Genre:** Fantasy/Romance\n   - **Director:** Guillermo del Toro\n   - **Synopsis:** A unique love story between a mute cleaning lady and an amphibious creature held in captivity at a high-security government laboratory during the Cold War.\n   - **Highlights:** Praised for its visual style, storytelling, and performances. It won four Academy Awards, including Best Picture and Best Director.\n\n3. **Dunkirk**\n   - **Genre:** War/Drama\n   - **Director:** Christopher Nolan\n   - **Synopsis:** A gripping portrayal of the Dunkirk evacuation during World War II, showcasing the resilience and bravery of soldiers and civilians alike.\n   - **Highlights:** Noted for its intense pacing, practical effects, and Hans Zimmer\u2019s powerful score. It received multiple Oscar nominations, winning three.\n\n4. **Logan**\n   - **Genre:** Superhero/Action\n   - **Director:** James Mangold\n   - **Synopsis:** A darker, more introspective take on the Wolverine character, set in a future where mutants are nearly extinct. It explores themes of aging, redemption, and legacy.\n   - **Highlights:** Celebrated for its mature storytelling, character development, and Hugh Jackman\u2019s performance. It is often regarded as one of the best superhero films.\n\n5. **Coco**\n   - **Genre:** Animation/Family\n   - **Directors:** Lee Unkrich and Adrian Molina\n   - **Synopsis:** Follows a young boy named Miguel who dreams of becoming a musician despite his family\u2019s baffling generations-old ban on music. He embarks on a journey to the Land of the Dead to uncover the truth behind his family history.\n   - **Highlights:** Lauded for its vibrant animation, heartfelt story, and respectful portrayal of Mexican culture. It won two Academy Awards, including Best Animated Feature and Best Original Song.\n\n6. **Wonder Woman**\n   - **Genre:** Superhero/Action\n   - **Director:** Patty Jenkins\n   - **Synopsis:** Chronicles the origin of Diana Prince (Wonder Woman) and her journey to stop World War I, showcasing her powers and heroic deeds.\n   - **Highlights:** Praised for its direction, performances (especially Gal Gadot), and empowering portrayal of its female lead. It was a major box office success and received positive reviews.\n\n7. **Spider-Man: Homecoming**\n   - **Genre:** Superhero/Action\n   - **Director:** Jon Watts\n   - **Synopsis:** Follows Peter Parker balancing high school life with his role as Spider-Man as he faces the villainous Vulture.\n   - **Highlights:** Enjoyed for its youthful energy, humor, and integration into the Marvel Cinematic Universe. It resonated well with both critics and audiences.\n\n8. **Baby Driver**\n   - **Genre:** Action/Crime\n   - **Director:** Edgar Wright\n   - **Synopsis:** Centers on a talented getaway driver, Baby, who relies on music to be the best in the business, as he seeks freedom from a life of crime.\n   - **Highlights:** Acclaimed for its stylish direction, innovative action sequences, and eclectic soundtrack. It received praise for seamlessly blending music with narrative.\n\n9. **Blade Runner 2049**\n   - **Genre:** Sci-Fi/Thriller\n   - **Director:** Denis Villeneuve\n   - **Synopsis:** A sequel to the 1982 classic, it follows a new Blade Runner, LAPD Officer K, as he unearths a long-buried secret that leads him to search for Rick Deckard.\n   - **Highlights:** Celebrated for its stunning visuals, thoughtful storytelling, and deep philosophical themes. Although it had a more moderate box office performance, it received widespread critical acclaim.\n\n10. **Lady Bird**\n    - **Genre:** Drama/Comedy\n    - **Director:** Greta Gerwig\n    - **Synopsis:** A coming-of-age story about a high school senior navigating the complexities of friendship, family, and her aspirations to attend college in New York City.\n    - **Highlights:** Praised for its authentic portrayal of adolescence, strong performances (especially Saoirse Ronan), and heartfelt narrative. It received multiple award nominations, including five Academy Award nods.\n\nThese films stood out in 2017 for their storytelling, direction, performances, and overall impact on audiences and critics alike. Whether you're interested in thought-provoking dramas, thrilling action, or heartfelt animations, 2017 offered a rich selection of high-quality Hollywood films.",
